Case called @ 3:01 PM Defendant Brian Keith Harrington in court, in custody.  Attorney Morgan Rae in court for Brian Keith Harrington.  Attorney Dennis Ryan in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Ruth Zouski appears amicus curiae. Competency report received by all parties. Hearing scheduled to receive testimony from the doctor regarding that report. Dr. Brooke Lundbohm sworn in for testimony. ADA Ryan questions the doctor. Atty Rae questions the doctor. ADA Ryan further questions the doctor. Atty Rae further questions the doctor. Statement by ADA Ryan. Statement by Atty Zouski - there is potential housing for the defendant if he is released to the competency restoration program on an outpatient basis.Statement by Atty Rae. The Court finds the defendant not competent, likely to regain competence within the statutory time limits. The Court orders the defendant's participation in the Outpatient Competency Restoration Program. The Court amends the cash bond to a $10,000 Sig Bond with the same conditions. 65 days CFTS.

Case called @ 2:21 PM: Defendant Brian Keith Harrington in court, in custody.  Attorney Morgan Rae in court for Brian Keith Harrington.  Attorney Dennis Ryan in court for State of Wisconsin. Both parties have received the competency report and reviewed it. No objection to the findings by ADA Ryan. No objection to the findings by Atty Rae. The defendant does not believe he is competent to proceed. The Court finds that the DE is not competent to proceed at this point but is likely to regain competency. Statement by ADA Ryan regarding medication administration. Statement by Atty Rae regarding medication compliance and outpatient treatment. The Court will not follow the recommendation without a further hearing regarding the DE's ability to regain competency on an outpatient basis in conjunction with the medication order. The Court would like testimony from the examining physician. Follow up Comp. Hearing scheduled - NOH given.
